Just asking.  I honestly know nothing about it.

@Francis 

It would be considered a silk rather than a wool. Since the clue is "Its wool is the world's rarest natural fiber", that just means that there's no correct answer to the clue at all. 

It's as if the clue were "The largest of the 50 states by land area, its southern border is the Rio Grande".

@JT 

